title: 820-3476-A fan spin,vcore, no light on usb
message:
820-3476-a, board looks good, cant see any corrosion, board turns on and off with power button, will pram reset.
Getting vcore, cpu is getting warm not hot. No light on usb mouse.

Is this worth attempting?, the looking i've done around the forum suggests it may not be

title: 820-3476-A fan spin,vcore, no light on usb
message: How do you know it does a PRAM reset? Voltage on Vcore?

title: 820-3476-A fan spin,vcore, no light on usb
message: Judging from fan activity, will spin as normal on start, but with PRAM reset will start, power off and start again like it should. vcore 1.75v

title: 820-3476-A fan spin,vcore, no light on usb
message: Fan does not stop when you do a PRAM reset as far as I know. What is the history on this thing?

title: 820-3476-A fan spin,vcore, no light on usb
message: Was picked up from a computer repair store when they closed, device looked somewhat impact damaged, no repairs attempted so far as much as i can tell.

title: 820-3476-A fan spin,vcore, no light on usb
message: If this really was impact damage then it is a waste of time.

title: 820-3476-A fan spin,vcore, no light on usb
message: Check U1950, often the cause of a CPU running cold/no post.
